---
layout: base.njk
title: "Design System"
description: "Tokens, components, and interaction guidelines for Let’s Talk CDC."
canonicalPath: "/design-system/"
head_extra: |
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/pages/style-guide.css">
---
<section class="hero-section">
  <div class="prose">
    <p class="type-title text-muted">Design Language</p>
    <h1 class="type-display">CDC Manual Design System</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      Shared tokens and interaction patterns power a consistent, accessible experience across the CDC learning series.
      Use this page as the source of truth when building new pages, illustrations, or interactive labs.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-style-guide container">
  <div class="intro">
    <h2 class="type-title">Foundations</h2>
    <p>
      Core decisions for typography, color, and spacing. Tokens live in <code>src/assets/css/styles.css</code> and cascade across light and dark themes.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="tokens-grid" aria-label="Color Tokens">
    {% set colors = [
      { name: 'Accent / Primary', token: '--accent-primary' },
      { name: 'Accent / Hover', token: '--accent-hover' },
      { name: 'Surface / Base', token: '--bg-primary' },
      { name: 'Surface / Secondary', token: '--bg-secondary' },
      { name: 'Text / Primary', token: '--text-primary' },
      { name: 'Text / Secondary', token: '--text-secondary' },
      { name: 'Border', token: '--border-color' },
      { name: 'Success', token: '--success-color' },
      { name: 'Warning', token: '--warning-color' },
      { name: 'Danger', token: '--danger-color' }
    ] %}
    {% for color in colors %}
      <article class="token-card" aria-label="{{ color.name }}">
        <div class="token-sample">
          <strong>{{ color.name }}</strong>
          <span>var({{ color.token }})</span>
        </div>
        <div class="color-swatch" style="background: var({{ color.token }});"></div>
      </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <div class="typography-list" aria-label="Typography Scale">
    {% set typeRamp = [
      { label: 'Display', class: 'type-display', token: '--type-display', sample: 'Reliable CDC pipelines begin with clarity.' },
      { label: 'Hero', class: 'type-hero', token: '--type-hero', sample: 'Bring change data capture to production.' },
      { label: 'Title', class: 'type-title', token: '--type-title', sample: 'Exactly-once semantics' },
      { label: 'Heading', class: 'type-heading', token: '--type-heading', sample: 'Snapshot checklists' },
      { label: 'Body', class: '', token: '--type-body', sample: 'CDC enables real-time data movement with minimal source impact.' },
      { label: 'Small', class: '', token: '--type-sm', sample: 'Used for meta text, captions, and data labels.' }
    ] %}
    {% for item in typeRamp %}
      <article class="typography-item">
        <p class="{{ item.class }}">{{ item.sample }}</p>
        <code>{{ item.label }} · var({{ item.token }})</code>
      </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <div class="utility-grid">
    <section class="utility-card" aria-labelledby="layout-tokens">
      <h3 id="layout-tokens" class="type-heading">Spacing & Radius</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">Spacing tokens scale layouts without hard-coded pixels.</p>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>var(--space-xs) → micro gutters</li>
        <li>var(--space-md) → block padding</li>
        <li>var(--space-2xl) → hero bands</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-muted">Use radius tokens for components:<br>--radius-sm, --radius-md, --radius-lg, --radius-full.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="utility-card" aria-labelledby="button-styles">
      <h3 id="button-styles" class="type-heading">Button States</h3>
      <div class="sample-button-row">
        <a class="button" href="#">Primary</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="#">Secondary</a>
        <a class="button ghost" href="#">Ghost</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-muted">Primary buttons carry the main action per view. Secondary and ghost styles support ancillary actions.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="utility-card" aria-labelledby="chips">
      <h3 id="chips" class="type-heading">Pills & Chips</h3>
      <div class="utility-chip-row">
        <button class="pill" type="button">Beginner</button>
        <button class="pill" type="button">Practitioner</button>
        <button class="pill" aria-pressed="true" type="button">Deep Dive</button>
      </div>
      <p class="text-muted">Use pills to filter content or denote states. Remember to set <code>aria-pressed</code> when toggled.</p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <section class="utility-card" aria-labelledby="accessibility">
    <h3 id="accessibility" class="type-heading">Accessibility Checklist</h3>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>Maintain 4.5:1 contrast for body text in both themes.</li>
      <li>Use <code>focus-visible</code> outlines that meet WCAG sizing.</li>
      <li>Respect reduced motion via the <code>.reduce-motion</code> utility.</li>
      <li>Prefer semantic HTML and landmark roles for layout.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</section>
